text_Original:
What I love about the prospect of the Metaverse (as shown here) is that, fundamentally, it simply gives a new meaning to the concept of "here". 

Very soon the place that we call "here" - as far as us interacting with others - will be a meeting point where we feel like we are in one same place, together, when we're actually far apart. We're now too close to that place. A place where we're no longer within ourselves while tethered-to-somewhere-there, but actually sharing one common place that more truly feels like "here". 

Welcome to the HereVerse. :)
